en_924336_0	Security Force Headquarters - Jaffna (SFHQ-J) using its machinery and much-needed manpower at the request of ‘Friends of Jaffna’ and Vadukkodai South West Farmers Association completely renovated the tank near the Arali Shettiarmadam Periyathambiran temple in Vadukkoddai.
en_924336_1	Both organizations after meeting Major General Dharshana Hettiarrachchi, Commander, Security Forces - Jaffna (SF-J) sought the Army assistance for renovation of this farming tank which remains almost abandoned for some time.
en_924336_2	Its water has been earlier used for cultivation purposes but after it was neglected, farmers had been forced to get down water from remote areas for agricultural needs.
en_924336_3	District Secretariat for Jaffna agreed to provide funds for renovation work following discussions they have had with representatives farmers.
en_924336_4	Army troops with heavy machinery and equipment effectively carried out the project and completed it within a few weeks.
en_924336_5	The formal handover ceremony of the resurrected tank took place a few days ago during a ceremony near the tank.
en_924336_6	Major General Dharshana Hettiarrachchi, Mr S Balachandran, Consul General of India in Jaffna, Major General Roshan Seneviratne, General Officer Commanding, 51 Division, senior Officers, Other Ranks and a large gathering of farmers in the area participated in the event.
